articles.description:
This talk of Burns this and Volcker that ignores how much of a disaster the US’ fiscal situation is.
Last time Fed debt/GDP was this high bonds delivered a few decades of negative real returns as the government debased the dollar.
The Fed can’t tighten its way out of this mess.


KKGB (Carlo Casio): Lael Brainard can’t control her Burns instincts. Could be useful to study inflation volatility regimes and how they shift. Here the 70s
